title: Barry Lyndon
overview: An Irish rogue wins the heart of a rich widow and assumes her dead husband's aristocratic position in 18th-century England.

title: The Searchers
overview: An American Civil War veteran embarks on a journey to rescue his niece from the Comanches.

title: Apollo 13
overview: NASA must devise a strategy to return Apollo 13 to Earth safely after the spacecraft undergoes massive internal damage putting the lives of the three astronauts on board in jeopardy.

title: The Message
overview: This epic historical drama chronicles the life and times of Prophet Muhammad and serves as an introduction to early Islamic history.

title: The Ten Commandments
overview: Moses, an Egyptian Prince, learns of his true heritage as a Hebrew and his divine mission as the deliverer of his people.

title: The Last Emperor
overview: The story of the final Emperor of China.

title: The Treasure of the Sierra Madre
overview: Two Americans searching for work in Mexico convince an old prospector to help them mine for gold in the Sierra Madre Mountains.

title: The Longest Day
overview: The events of D-Day, told on a grand scale from both the Allied and German points of view.

title: The Fall
overview: In a hospital on the outskirts of 1920s Los Angeles, an injured stuntman begins to tell a fellow patient, a little girl with a broken arm, a fantastic story of five mythical heroes. Thanks to his fractured state of mind and her vivid imagination, the line between fiction and reality blurs as the tale advances.

title: Ben-Hur
overview: After a Jewish prince is betrayed and sent into slavery by a Roman friend, he regains his freedom and comes back for revenge.

title: The African Queen
overview: In WWI Africa, a gin-swilling riverboat captain is persuaded by a strait-laced missionary to use his boat to attack an enemy warship.

title: Hidden Figures
overview: The story of a team of female African-American mathematicians who served a vital role in NASA during the early years of the U.S. space program.

title: Inglourious Basterds
overview: In Nazi-occupied France during World War II, a plan to assassinate Nazi leaders by a group of Jewish U.S. soldiers coincides with a theatre owner's vengeful plans for the same.

title: Inherit the Wind
overview: Based on a real-life case in 1925, two great lawyers argue the case for and against a science teacher accused of the crime of teaching evolution.

title: The King's Speech
overview: The story of King George VI, his impromptu ascension to the throne of the British Empire in 1936, and the speech therapist who helped the unsure monarch overcome his stammer.

title: The Last King of Scotland
overview: Based on the events of the brutal Ugandan dictator Idi Amin's regime as seen by his personal physician during the 1970s.

title: Big Fish
overview: A frustrated son tries to determine the fact from fiction in his dying father's life.

title: Empire of the Sun
overview: A young English boy struggles to survive under Japanese occupation during World War II.

title: The Bridge on the River Kwai
overview: British POWs are forced to build a railway bridge across the river Kwai for their Japanese captors, not knowing that the allied forces are planning to destroy it.

title: Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows: Part 2
overview: Harry, Ron, and Hermione search for Voldemort's remaining Horcruxes in their effort to destroy the Dark Lord as the final battle rages on at Hogwarts.
